.TH pulsar 1 "Apache Pulsar" "Version 4.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pulsar \- Apache Pulsar broker launcher
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pulsar
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Apache Pulsar is a distributed messaging and streaming platform offering
low latency, high throughput, and scalable pub-sub messaging.

The \fBpulsar\fR wrapper script (provided by the \fBapache-pulsar\fR package)
is used to start Pulsar components such as the standalone server, the broker,
the proxy, and other subsystems.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B standalone
Runs the all-in-one developer Pulsar instance with
embedded ZooKeeper and BookKeeper.

.TP
.B broker
Starts the Pulsar broker service.

.TP
.B proxy
Starts the Pulsar proxy service.

.TP
.B bookie
Starts the BookKeeper storage server.

.SH OPTIONS
Options vary depending on the chosen command.
Run:
.RS
pulsar <command> --help
.RE
for detailed usage.

.SH FILES
.TP
/etc/apache-pulsar/
Configuration files.
.TP
/usr/lib/apache-pulsar/
Apache Pulsar JAR files, libraries and runtime data.
.TP
/usr/bin/pulsar
Main launcher script.
.TP
/lib/systemd/system/apache-pulsar.service
Systemd unit file.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
PULSAR_LOG_DIR
Override log directory.
.TP
PULSAR_CONF
Override configuration directory.

.SH EXAMPLES
Start standalone Pulsar:
.RS
pulsar standalone
.RE

